<CENTER>


<h3>Talk of the Town</h3>

<b>The Heritage Foundation: Providing Practical Ideas for America's Future</b>
</center>
<P>
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;	As the nation's leading think tank, The Heritage Foundation's impact on public policy is more pronounced than ever. As <I>The Wall 
Street Journal</I> wrote recently, "No policy shop has more clout than the conservative Heritage 
Foundation."
<p>
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;	Indeed, many of the 104th Congress' plans for balancing 
the budget and scaling back big government began at Heritage. By providing official Washington 
with timely research and analysis, Heritage has become a primary information source for America's 
lawmakers.
<p>
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;	Heritage's people are more than just well-informed and 
well-educated. Many have hands-on government experience. They are doers as well as thinkers.  
Players, not just spectators. 
<p>

&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;	If you need a thought-provoking, articulate expert to 
discuss today's important issues, The Heritage Foundation is the place to turn. Contact 
<a href="mailto:moebiusw@heritage.org">Wanda Moebius</a> at (202) 675-1761 to book a speaker.
     
 <P>
<a name="top">
<CENTER><h3>Topics:</h3><br>
<B>You may click on a specific topic or scroll through the entire document.</B></CENTER>
	<p>
<img src="blueball.gif" alt=""><a href="#washington"><b>Washington's Marketplace of Ideas</b></a>			
<p><ul>
<li>The Conservative Revolution
<li>Washington Politics
<li>Restoring Power to the States 
</ul>
<P>
<img src="blueball.gif" alt=""><b><a href="#economy">The Economy and Society</a></b>			 			
	
