<title>Cyber Person Welcome -- Heritage</title>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg"><center>
<h2><i>Heritage CyberPersonality Forum</i></h2>

<img src="/heritage/miller.gif" align=left hspace=5></a>
<P>

<code>[<a href="/heritage/cyberp/cyb-fam.html">Hot Issues</a>][<A HREF="http://www.townhall.com/townhall/wgw-forum/ac/dispatch.cgi/thf-cyber/">Forum</A>][<a href="/townhall/wgw-forum/ac/dispatch.cgi/_user/addForm/short">Register</A> -- Free!][<a href="#about">About</a> Forums][<a href="/heritage/cyberp/cybarch.html">Column Archive</a>]</code> </CENTER> <P>


Welcome to the Town Hall CyberPersonality site!  I can assure you that this is certainly a new venture for me.  I've heard of "talking heads" from the likes of "Capitol Gang," and what used to be "MacNeil-Lehrer," but an on-line Internet personality is one of newest ways The Heritage Foundation would like to get past the limited amount of media coverage of hot issues and tell you what is really happening in Washington, on Capitol Hill, in the White House, and in policy circles.
<P>
A little bit about me -- I'm <a href="/heritage/cyberbio.html">Karen Czarnecki Miller</a>, and I'm primarily responsible for maintaining contact with the <a href="http://www.whitehouse.gov">Clinton Administration</a>, educating the presidential campaigns on important policy issues, and overseeing The Heritage Foundation's <a href="/heritage/jobs/jobs.html">Job Bank</a>. I also serve as a spokesman for the Foundation on Heritage proposals and research findings in all areas of the Foundation's study.<p>


I'd like to tell you a little bit about what you can expect to see when you come to this site.  Of course, over the next several months, I'll be doing some fine-tuning to make this as interesting and informative as possible.  I'd like to hear your thoughts on what you'd like to see, and what would help you to keep on top of current issues. 
<p>
Twice a week -- on Tuesday and Friday -- I will be on-line to discuss hot topics on the Hill and elsewhere, and answer your questions.  I am also planning to post research materials, discuss what opinion leaders are saying, interview guests on politics and policy, and much more!  
<p>
What would you like to see? Please <a href="mailto:gabrona@heritage.org">email</a> your thoughts to me, or to <a href="mailto: gabrona@heritage.org">Andy Gabron</a>, who helps me with research
 for this page. I look forward to hearing from you! 
<p>
<a href="cyberbio.html">Want more background? Read my biography</a>
<p>
<a name="about"><center><h3>About the Forums</h3></center>
<p>
For best results, you should keep the following in mind:<p>
<ul>
<li>Anyone may read the contents of the  <A HREF="http://www.townhall.com/townhall/wgw-forum/ac/dispatch.cgi/thf-cyber/">Forums</a>.  To post a message, you will need to <a href="/townhall/wgw-forum/ac/dispatch.cgi/_user/addForm/short">register</a>.<p>
<li>To change your password, log in and select your name from the <a href="/townhall/wgw-forum/ac/dispatch.cgi/_user">registered users</a> list.  Choose the "modify" button that appears on the linked page.   <p> 
<li>Using the procedure listed above, you can modify how the forum looks and acts.<p> 
<li><b>Important Note:</b> Unfortunately, registered users of Town Hall's old Town Meetings or Heritage's Cyber Personality forums will need to <a href="/townhall/wgw-forum/ac/dispatch.cgi/_user/addForm/short">re-register</a> to use this application.  Fortunately, doing so is easy and quick. 
</ul>
Follow the links below to enter the meeting area of your choice.  Please note, your use of these areas implies your acceptance of <a href="http://www.townhall.com/townhall/wgw-forum/ac/conduct.html">the rules of conduct</a> that govern their use.
Please send any comments to <a href="mailto:gabrona@heritage.org">Andy Gabron</a>.
<center>
<br><br>









<p>
<code>[<a href="/heritage/cyberp/cyb-fam.html">Hot Issues</a>][<A HREF="http://www.townhall.com/townhall/wgw-forum/ac/dispatch.cgi/thf-cyber/">Forum</A>][<a href="/townhall/wgw-forum/ac/dispatch.cgi/_user/addForm/short">Register</a> -- Free!][<a href="#about">About</a> Forums][<a href="/heritage/cyberp/cybarch.html">Column Archive</a>]   
</code><P>
