<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">
<center><img src="/heritage/thf_log2.gif">

<h2>Join the Heritage Foundation</h2><br>
<p>
<h3>A tax-exempt public policy research institute dedicated to free enterprise, limited government, traditional American values, and a strong national defense.</h3></center>

<p>

"Heritage is, without question, the most wide-reaching conservative organization in the 'war of ideas' and one which has had a tremendous impact, not just on Washington, but literally across the planet."<b>
<i>-- Speaker of the House Newt Gingrich</i></b>
<p>
"Heritage is Washington's leading conservative think tank."
<b><i>--New York Times</i></b>

<p>
"Success in politics is about issues, ideas, and the vision we have for our country and the world.  In fact, the very sum and substance of the work of The Heritage Foundation."
<b><i>--Ronald Reagan</i></b>
<p>

"When Heritage talks, Washington listens."
<b><i>--Jack Kemp</i></b>
<p>

"Heritage is the best organization in Washington in terms of generating ideas, generating analysis, and having substantial impact on the policy debates.  Heritage is always reliable....It's always there when you need it....That's why it is so critical that it continue to thrive and that you continue to support it."
<b><i>--Bill Bennett</i></b>
<p>

"No institution has had more influence than The Heritage Foundation.  I have taken many of my ideas from you."
<br><b><i>--Senator Phil Gramm</i></b>
<p>

"The Heritage Foundation holds unprecedented influence both in the House of Representatives and in Congress in general."

<b><i>--Representative Steve Largent</i></b>

<h3>	HOW DOES HERITAGE INFLUENCE WASHINGTON?</h3>
<p>

	<i>Heritage publishes more than 200 timely, well researched studies each year on issues being debated by decision makers in Washington.  Heritage papers on cutting taxes and spending, reforming Congress, cultural policy, health care, education, the environment, foreign and defense policy, and other issues are used by more than 6,000 key decision makers in the Nation's Capital.

<p>
	Heritage studies are full of data, statistics and well-reasoned arguments for government policies based on free-market principles.  Heritage experts write papers, testify before Congress, appear on television news programs and radio talk shows, provide private briefings for Members of Congress, and are quoted in thousands of newspaper articles each year.  </i>
<p>

	<h3>WHAT  ARE  HERITAGE'S  MARKETS?</h3>
<p>
<b>Primary</b><br>
<p><ul>
<li>	Members of Congress and their staffs.<br>

<li>	The President and the Executive Branch agencies.<br>

<li>	The news media.<br></ul>

<p>
<b>Secondary</b><br>
<ul>
<li>	Academics across the country.<br>

<li>	Other conservative organizations.<br>

<li>	State politicians and think tanks.<br></ul>
<p>

<h3>	WHO  SUPPORTS  THE  HERITAGE  FOUNDATION?</h3>

	<p>
	More than 200,000 individuals, foundations, and corporations who believe that America's problems can be solved by adhering to those principles which made America great:  free enterprise, limited government, traditional American values, and a strong national defense.  The Heritage Foundation does not accept government money.<p>



<h3><a href="/heritage/donat.html">	JOIN THE HERITAGE FOUNDATION</a></h3>
<p>
	Members of The Heritage Foundation have the satisfaction of knowing their financial investment in Heritage is making America a more politically conservative nation.<p>

	Heritage Members share a commitment to the values which built our country:  free enterprise, limited government, individual freedom, traditional American values, and a strong national defense.  Through The Heritage Foundation, dedicated conservatives across the nation are joining together to advance these principles in the Nation's Capital.<p>

	The Heritage Foundation does not accept any government funds.  <p>


<b>President's Club<br>
$1,000</b><br>

	Benefits:<br>
<ul>
	<li>		Invitations to semi-annual President's Club meetings in Washington
featuring such speakers as Newt Gingrich, Jack Kemp, Bill Bennett, Bill Kristol,
Phil Gramm and other leading conservatives.<br>
	<li>		Monthly reports from the President of The Heritage Foundation.<br>
	<li>		Advance access to all Heritage publications. Longer publications, such as books, will be mailed to you.<br></ul>
<p>
