<body bgcolor="ffffff">
<head>
<title>NR Extra!</title>
</head>
<body>
<p> 
<center><img src="/nationalreview/images/extra.gif" ALT="NR Extra!"></center>
<br>
<br>
<!-------------------------------------------------------------->
<center><b>December 17, 1996</b></center>
<HR WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<P>
<blockquote>
 <LI>





 Last month President Clinton came clean on Bosnia, finally revealing that 8,500 U.S. troops would remain past the original December 20 deadline. The original deployment of 35,000 Americans had "succeeded beyond our expectations," he said, but a follow-on force, more limited in size and mandate, was required for another 18 months to ensure political stability. IFOR (Implementation Force) will be renamed SFOR (Stabilization Force). The problems, needless to say, are manybeginning with Congressional anger at Clinton's denials before the election that any such extension was planned. More  important, the political provisions of the Dayton Accords, which aim at creating a unitary, multi-ethnic Bosnian state, are beginning to unravel. U.S. training and equipping of the Bosnianswhich the President had promised Congresshas barely begun, leaving them still dependent on foreign troops. The President may get his way, given the difficulty of cutting off funds and overriding a veto, but he compounds all his risks, at home and in Bosnia, unless he keeps his promise this time and gives the Bosnians the wherewithal to defend themselves.
<P>
<LI> A study published recently in the <I>American Journal of Public Health</I> suggests that racial discrimination by whites against blacks causes high blood pressure in blacks. Curiously, it was among blacks who were unaware that they had suffered discrimination that the effect was most pronounced. Dr. Nancy Krieger explained that this was a consequence of "suppressed or internalized response." The study did not address the effect that black-on-white crimewhich according to Irving Horowitz in the January 1995 issue of <I>Society</I> in 60 times greater than white-on-black crimehas on the health of whites.
</blockquote>


